      • createListener

        public static <T extends net.dv8tion.jda.core.events.Event> Waiter.WaiterListener<T> createListener(@Nonnull
                                                                                                    net.dv8tion.jda.core.JDA shard,
                                                                                                    @Nonnull
                                                                                                    java.lang.Class<T> eventClass,
                                                                                                    @Nullable
                                                                                                    java.util.function.Predicate<T> checker,
                                                                                                    @Nullable
                                                                                                    java.util.function.Consumer<T> onSuccess,
                                                                                                    @Nullable
                                                                                                    java.lang.Runnable onTimeout,
                                                                                                    long timeout,
                                                                                                    boolean disposable)
        Create a listener that will wait for a specific event and can perform various checks and action during this process. It uses the shard's pool to schedule the timeout.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of event to listen to.
        Parameters:
        shard - The shard where the event is supposed to happen.
        eventClass - The class of the event to listen to.
        checker - (Optional) A checker to say if the event is valid or not.
        onSuccess - (Optional) Code to execute if the listener successfully catch an event.
        onTimeout - (Optional) Code to execute when the listener will timeout (if a timeout is set).
        timeout - The life time in millisecond of the listener. After that, it will be destroyed. 0 for infinite.
        disposable - If true, the listener will trigger at most one time and then complete, otherwise it will continue until it times out.
        Returns:
        A new WaiterListener configured with the given parameters.
